# No direct merges to main

`main` is branch-protected. All changes reach production through a PR the user reviews and merges.

## Never do without explicit user request

- `gh pr merge` (any merge strategy)
- `git push origin main` or push directly to `main`
- `gh workflow run Deploy` or other production deploy triggers

## When planning a new feature

Choose the branch per `.cursor/rules/branch-lifecycle.mdc` (merged → new `feat/*` off `main`; otherwise continue the current branch). Never plan work that commits directly on `main`. When unsure which case applies, ask before branching.

## Required workflow

1. Resolve the branch per branch-lifecycle (new `feat/*` off `main`, or continue the existing branch)
2. Implement changes and open a PR with a clear summary and test plan
3. **Stop** — wait for the user to review, or enable auto-merge
   (`gh pr merge --auto --squash`) after they approve opening the PR so green
   CI merges without babysitting (see `pr-auto-merge`). Do not merge without
   `--auto` unless they explicitly ask to merge now.
4. Do not re-trigger deploy after opening the PR unless the user asks

## Deploy / infra changes

Changes to `scripts/deploy.sh`, `.github/workflows/deploy.yml`, or VPS setup scripts always go through a PR. Never merge or deploy them autonomously.
